
Vim configuration and plugins
------------------------------------

This setup has been tested on OS X and Ubuntu.

Installation

1. Clone this repository
2. Run git submodule init && git submodule update
3. Setup command -t
	a. go to vim/bundle/plugin-command-t/ruby/command-t
	b. run 'ruby extconf.rb'
	c. run 'make'

4. Sym links
	a. /vim => ~/.vim
	b. /vimvrc => ~/.vimrc
	c. /gvimrc => ~/.gvimrc (If using gvim/macvim)


Requirements

	- git
	- ruby
	- vim/gvim/macvim

Plugins

	- command-t: File Searching (<leader> t)
	- nerdtree: File Brownsing (:NERDTree /some/path)


Note: When setting up command-t on Ubuntu, you may need to install ruby1.8-dev when running extconf.rb.
'sudo apt-get install ruby1.8dev'

Based off of gavim - https://github.com/gaveen/gavim
